  "prompt": "What is the necessity of introducing 2000 rupee notes?",
  "response": "The introduction of the 2000 rupee note in India in 2016, following the demonetization of 500 and 1000 rupee notes, was primarily aimed at:\n\n*   **Quickly replenishing the currency in circulation:** Demonetization removed a large portion of the circulating currency. The 2000 rupee note allowed the government to remonetize the economy faster than if they had only printed lower denomination notes.\n*   **Meeting the transaction needs of the economy:** A high-value note was seen as necessary to facilitate large transactions, given the sudden shortage of currency.\n\nHowever, the 2000 rupee note was later discontinued in 2023, with the Reserve Bank of India (RBI) citing concerns about it being used for illicit transactions and its limited use in regular transactions.",
